## Code Quality Standards

### Do's ✅
- Write self-documenting code with clear names
- Keep components focused and single-purpose
- Use TypeScript strictly (no `any` types)
- Implement error boundaries for production
- Add loading and error states to async components

### Don'ts ❌
- Don't use inline styles (use Tailwind utilities)
- Avoid deep nesting (max 3-4 levels)
- Don't duplicate utility combinations (extract to component)
- Never skip accessibility features for speed
- Don't use `!important` in Tailwind classes